data.name: The Halfway House & Mulberry Restaurant
data.description: The Halfway House has been a popular establishment for over eighty years. Over the years it has been modernised to the highest standards of traditional decor including open fireplaces, function room and restaurant.The Halfway House is famous throughout north Dublin area for its friendly atmosphere, its efficient and courteous staff and its high quality carvery food.The Mulberry Restaurant is open Wed-Sat for A La Carte & early bird menu. On Sundays we serve Lunch and A La Carte.

data.name: Appatizers Bistro Cafe
data.description: Everyone needs somewhere they can go to catch up with friends, read a book or spend some time alone, and that’s exactly what we had in mind when we started out. Located in Royal Canal Park, Ashtown, Dublin 15, we opened Appatizers Bistro and Café with the hopes it would become a friendly neighbourhood restaurant. From freshly baked treats and delicious coffee, to a tasty dinner… we’ve got everything you need right here, with an emphasis on quality fresh ingredients cooked well, and served by pleasant staff. In the current climate we are only able to offer a take away option, we’re readapting how to do business but our core values haven’t changed, and we hope that we are still meeting your expectations! Our menu is constantly evolving & changing so why not let us know what you’d like to see on there, we value your feedback? Lorna & all the team @ Appatizers
data.address: Pelletstown Ave Corner of Lock Keepers Walk, Dublin Ireland

data.name: The Lock Keeper
data.description: Nestled in the heart of Ashtown Village, Dublin 15, overlooking the Royal Canal, The Lock Keeper can be found at Lock #10. Steeped in heritage, this double lock was constructed c.1792. With quality stonework and attractive sloping edges Lock 10 is one of 46 along the Royal Canal and continues to be a testament to the skill of the craftsmen involved. Our bar is adjacent to the Lock Keepers Hous
